The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 11:15 a.m. Lima time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell 0.1 percent to 22,819.17. The
 MSCI All Peru Capped Index (MXPECAPD)  was little changed at 2,888.89.  Refineria La Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1)  (RELAPAC1 PE), the countryâ€™s
largest petroleum refinery, advanced to a one-week high after
oil climbed as tension with  Iran  threatens supplies and on signs
of a global economic recovery. Relapasa, as the company is
known, climbed 2 percent to 1.04 soles.  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian copper
exploration company, climbed 6.1 percent to 70 cents, the
highest in almost a year, as the metal advanced in  New York .
 Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , the Canadian exploration firm
with operations in Peru, added 1.9 percent to $1.08.  Minera IRL Ltd. (MIRL)  , a U.K. minerals explorer with a
gold mine in Peru, fell after the precious metal declined for
the first time in four days as demand for a haven eased amid
signs of strength in the  U.S. economy . Lima-based Minera
retreated 3.3 percent to $1.18.  To contact the reporter on this story:
